tman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20companies%2C%20OpenAI%20says%20it%20is%20run%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Four-structure%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecapped-profit%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20company%2C%20with%20its%20for-profit%20arm%20governed%20by%20a%20nonprofit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20announced%20in%20a%20March%202019%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Fopenai-lp%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20shedding%20its%20status%20as%20a%20typical%20nonprofit%20to%20better%20realize%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fabout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emission%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20building%20safe%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20(AGI)%20for%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20increase%20our%20ability%20to%20raise%20capital%20while%20still%20serving%20our%20mission%2C%20and%20no%20pre-existing%20legal%20structure%20we%20know%20of%20strikes%20the%20right%20balance%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BOur%20solution%20is%20to%20create%20OpenAI%20LP%20as%20a%20hybrid%20of%20a%20for-profit%20and%20nonprofit%E2%80%94which%20we%20are%20calling%20a%20'capped-profit'%C2%A0company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20OpenAI%20didn't%20respond%20to%20The%20Information's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman's%20leadership%20of%20the%20Microsoft-backed%20AI%20upstart%20has%20not%20been%20without%20controversy.%20In%20November%2C%20Altman%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-return-openai-ceo-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebriefly%20ousted%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20OpenAI's%20former%20board%20alleged%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Fopenai-announces-leadership-transition%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20consistently%20candid%20in%20his%20communications%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20years%2C%20Sam%20had%20made%20it%20really%20difficult%20for%20the%20board%20to%20actually%20do%20that%20job%20by%20withholding%20information%2C%20misrepresenting%20things%20that%20were%20happening%20at%20the%20company%2C%20in%20some%20cases%20outright%20lying%20to%20the%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20former%20OpenAI%20board%20member%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-board-member-details-sam-altman-lied-allegation-ousted-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHelen%20Toner%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20on%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.chtbl.com%2FTEDAI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20TED%20AI%20Show%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20podcast%20that%20aired%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToner%20said%20Altman%20was%20a%20deceptive%20figure%20who%20lied%20and%20hid%20information%20from%20the%20board%20%26quot%3Bmultiple%26quot%3B%20times.%20According%20to%20Toner%2C%20OpenAI's%20board%20was%20kept%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20ChatGPT's%20release%20in%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20board%20only%20learned%20about%20the%20chatbot's%20existence%2C%20like%20everybody%20else%2C%20when%20news%20of%20its%20release%20began%20spreading%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fsama%2Fstatus%2F1598038815599661056%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20on%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToner%2C%20who%20left%20the%20board%20shortly%20after%20Altman%20was%20reinstated%20as%20CEO%2C%20also%20accused%20him%20of%20lying%20about%20his%20financial%20interests%20in%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSam%20didn't%20inform%20the%20board%20that%20he%20owned%20the%20OpenAI%20Startup%20Fund%2C%20even%20though%20he%20constantly%20was%20claiming%20to%20be%20an%20independent%20board%20member%20with%20no%20financial%20interest%20in%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Toner%20said%2C%20referencing%20the%20company's%20venture%20capital%20fund%20for%20AI%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2029%2C%20OpenAI%20revealed%20in%20an%20SEC%20filing%20that%20Altman%20no%20longer%20owned%20or%20controlled%20the%20venture%20capital%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Axios%20that%20the%20fund's%20initial%20ownership%20structure%20was%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2024%2F04%2F01%2Fsam-altman-openai-startup-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etemporary%20arrangement%2C%20and%20involved%20no%20personal%20investment%20or%20financial%20interest%20from%20Sam%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20disappointed%20that%20Ms.%20Toner%20continues%20to%20revisit%20these%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20chairman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbret-taylor-resignation-salesforce-marc-benioff-showdown-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBret%20Taylor%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20the%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BOur%20focus%20remains%20on%20moving%20forward%20and%20pursuing%20OpenAI's%20mission%20to%20ensure%20AGI%20benefits%20all%20of%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20OpenAI%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-mulls-turning-openai-into-a-regular-company-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717041428000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6657e02a1cd3b1779041744a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-mulls-turning-openai-into-a-regular-company-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unlike%20most%20organizations%2C%20OpenAI%20says%20it%20is%20run%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcapped-profit%26quot%3B%20company%20where%20its%20for-profit%20arm%20is%20governed%