%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%20Falaschi%20served%20as%20the%20general%20manager%20of%20the%20Panoche%20Water%20District%20in%20Fresno%20and%20Merced%20Counties%2C%20located%20in%20central%20California%2C%20from%20around%201986%20to%202017.%20The%20public%20water%20district%20bought%20water%20from%20the%20federal%20government%20and%20collected%20drainage%20water%20from%20farms%2C%20both%20of%20which%20it%20then%20legally%20sold%20to%20farmers%20in%20the%20area%2C%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-edca%2Fpr%2Fformer-water-district-general-manager-pleads-guilty-conspiracy-commit-water-theft-and%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20attorney's%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20Eastern%20District%20of%20California%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20Falaschi%20discovered%20some%20of%20the%20federally%20owned%20water%20was%20leaking%20from%20an%20old%20pipe%20into%20a%20separate%20canal%2C%20the%20pipe%20was%20modified%20so%20it%20could%20be%20open%20and%20closed%2C%20allowing%20water%20to%20be%20taken%20%26quot%3Bon%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20attorney%20said%20Falaschi%20was%20responsible%20for%20stealing%20somewhere%20between%20%241.5%20million%20and%20%243.5%20million%20worth%20of%20water.%20Prosecutors%20also%20said%20that%20between%202011%20and%202016%20Falaschi%20was%20paid%20for%20water%20that%20he%20had%20sourced%20legally%2C%20but%20he%20did%20not%20report%20the%20income%20on%20his%20tax%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-edca%2Fmedia%2F1353436%2Fdl%3Finline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplea%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20Thursday%2C%20Falaschi%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20one%20count%20of%20conspiring%20to%20take%20federally%20owned%20water%20and%20one%20count%20of%20filing%20a%20false%20tax%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lawyer%20for%20Falaschi%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%20His%20sentencing%20is%20set%20for%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20plea%20provides%20some%20answers%2C%20many%20questions%20remain%20in%20the%20case%20that%20farmers%20in%20the%20San%20Joaquin%20Valley%20have%20been%20watching%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Falaschi%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-edca%2Fpress-release%2Ffile%2F1494726%2Fdl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindicted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%2C%20prosecutors%20painted%20him%20as%20the%20mastermind%20of%20a%20plot%20that%20lasted%20from%20around%201992%20to%202015%20in%20which%20more%20than%20%2425%2C000%2C000%20worth%20of%20water%20was%20stolen%20from%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20or%20more%20than%20130%2C000%20acre-feet%20of%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20said%20proceeds%20from%20the%20theft%2C%20which%20should've%20gone%20to%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20instead%20when%20to%20Falaschi%20and%20eight%20co-conspirators%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Bexorbitant%20salaries%2C%20fringe%20benefits%2C%20and%20personal%20expense%20reimbursements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fcalifornia%2Fstory%2F2024-04-28%2Fsan-joaquin-valley-official-accused-of-epic-california-water-heist%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20published%20a%20deep-dive%20into%20the%20alleged%20heist%20in%20April%2C%20reported%20that%20while%20some%20farmers%20were%20angry%20with%20Falaschi%2C%20others%20described%20him%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BRobin%20Hood%20of%20irrigation%2C%26quot%3B%20ensuring%20they%20could%20get%20the%20water%20they%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalaschi's%20plea%20agreement%20claims%20he's%20responsible%20for%20stealing%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20original%20%2425%20million%20prosecutors%20accused%20him%20of%20taking%20in%20the%20original%20indictment.%20The%20plea%20agreement%20also%20said%20Falaschi%20was%20one%20of%20several%20people%20involved%20in%20the%20misconduct%20and%20that%20he%20was%20unaware%20of%20the%20full%20extent%20of%20the%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20water%20Falaschi%20took%2C%20the%20plea%20agreement%20said%20almost%20all%20of%20it%20was%20taken%20to%20%26quot%3Bblend%20down%20and%20reuse%20drainage%20water%2C%20which%20helped%20protect%20farmland%20and%20improve%20water%20quality%20in%20the%20San%20Joaquin%20River.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20improved%20water%20quality%20contributed%20to%20the%20San%20Joaquin%20River%20being%20removed%20from%20the%20list%20of%20impaired%20waters%20under%20California's%20Clean%20Water%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20plea%20agreement%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20evidence%20that%20Mr.%20Falaschi%20directly%20benefitted%20from%20the%20misconduct.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fcalifornia%2Fstory%2F2024-05-28%2Fpanoche-official-pleads-guilty-in-water-theft-conspiracy%3Fsfmc_id%3D65329fc725b3640666af891d%26utm_id%3D35526484%26skey_id%3D12ff9948ec0105848e4dba7d6867e4d60c72154dcf243d4943c9fad16ab751ac%26utm_source%3DSailthru%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DALERT-Email-List-Who%2520else%2520was%2520stealing%3F%2520Conspiracy%2520plea%2520deepens%2520mystery%2520in%2520San%2520Joaquin%2520Valley%2520water%2520heist-20240528%26utm_term%3DAlert%2520-%2520News%2520Alerts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20the%20plea%20raises%20even%20more%20questions%20about%20who%20was%20stealing%20the%20water%2C%20who%20was%20making%20money%20off%20of%20it%2C%20and%20why%20it%20took%20the%20federal%20government%20so%20long%20to%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mystery%20surrounding%20the%20case%20continues%20as%20water%20use%20in%20the%20state%20coms%20under%20increasing%20scrutiny%2C%20with%20droughts%20and%20water%20shortages%20forcing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%